00:23:01.580 --> 00:23:05.970
And then they had them play various games
and dilemmas to see how well they could cooperate.

00:23:05.970 --> 00:23:11.080
And after moving together in synchrony, they
were better able, they could go further in

00:23:11.080 --> 00:23:13.360
these games that required extreme cooperation.

00:23:13.360 --> 00:23:17.450
Something that has very direct relevance to
any sort of collective effort, certainly in

00:23:17.450 --> 00:23:18.450
the business world.

00:23:18.450 --> 00:23:22.110
Moving together in time increases cooperation
and trust.

00:23:22.110 --> 00:23:28.760
Another study found that when you take rowers,
college level rowers and you have them row

00:23:28.760 --> 00:23:34.150
either in synchrony or not in synchrony, they
did it in a rowing tank so they could measure

00:23:34.150 --> 00:23:36.880
exactly how much force was being applied.

00:23:36.880 --> 00:23:40.370
They actually were able to deliver the same
amount of force, but then when they gave them

00:23:40.370 --> 00:23:42.740
the pain tolerance test afterwards.

00:23:42.740 --> 00:23:45.910
Those that had rowed in synchrony were able
to withstand more pain.

00:23:45.910 --> 00:23:50.710
In other words, it changes the endorphin system
which would be adaptive if this is a reflex

00:23:50.710 --> 00:23:51.990
for battle.

00:23:51.990 --> 00:23:54.930
Groups that move together in time can fight
together better, they can trust each other

00:23:54.930 --> 00:23:56.500
better.

00:23:56.500 --> 00:24:00.910
So we're changing some relatively low level
aspects of brain chemistry that would prepare

00:24:00.910 --> 00:24:03.320
individuals to be a part of a team in combat.

00:24:03.320 --> 00:24:09.140
Now in case you want any evidence that this
