00:27:46.770 --> 00:27:54.630
So, I think that there are some obvious benefits
of hivishness, just on its face now, I just

00:27:54.630 --> 00:27:59.640
signed on at the Business School at NYU, so
I haven't done the front line research on

00:27:59.640 --> 00:28:04.070
this directly but there are reasons to think
that hivishness is going to have these two

00:28:04.070 --> 00:28:05.620
major, major benefits.

00:28:05.620 --> 00:28:09.530
The first is almost, by definition, higher
social capital.

00:28:09.530 --> 00:28:13.900
Social capital is an important concept from
sociology, popularized in the 1990s.

00:28:13.900 --> 00:28:19.220
It refers to the trust that is found in relationships.

00:28:19.220 --> 00:28:24.110
So if two companies have, if one company has
more financial capital than another, but everything

00:28:24.110 --> 00:28:28.520
else is equal, more money in the bank is going
to let them beat out the other company.

00:28:28.520 --> 00:28:33.690
Similarly, if two companies are identical
and identical in financial capital, but one

00:28:33.690 --> 00:28:38.740
has more social capital, that is, people can
do as David said you need help, you ask for

00:28:38.740 --> 00:28:39.740
it, you get it.

00:28:39.740 --> 00:28:44.470
There's no backstabbing or there's no turf
guarding, that's social capital.

00:28:44.470 --> 00:28:47.700
If everything else is equal, that company
is going to beat out the other company.

00:28:47.700 --> 00:28:48.850
They're more efficient.

00:28:48.850 --> 00:28:54.200
So hivishness by definition is going to give
you higher social capital, which should generally

00:28:54.200 --> 00:28:57.740
translate into higher productivity and flexibility.

00:28:57.740 --> 00:29:01.640
Management can make changes and assume that
people will trust them, go along with it,

00:29:01.640 --> 00:29:04.429
not fight over well, should we change.

00:29:04.429 --> 00:29:05.900
You're a team, you're like one body.

00:29:05.900 --> 00:29:10.750
When I say move to the left, my right hand
